[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":536},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F":511,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F":520},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20260113\u002F3115395907\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":494,"date":495,"description":26,"extension":496,"lang":497,"meta":498,"navigation":163,"path":499,"readingMinutes":500,"seo":501,"standalone":502,"stem":503,"tags":504,"tldr":508,"updated":495,"url":509,"__hash__":510},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently.md","Tired of Opening Multiple Terminals to Run Commands? Use Concurrently","3115395917",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":487},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,46,49,83,86,101,107,111,122,208,217,311,318,322,325,391,401,405,412,474,483],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"concurrently","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fnode-concurrently\u002FGemini_Generated_Image_u5lg8zu5lg8zu5lg.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"As I take on more projects, I keep needing multiple terminal windows open for different commands — frontend dev server, backend API server, database service, and so on. Opening multiple windows and typing commands every time is incredibly annoying and wastes time. So here's an intro to concurrently.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"what-is-concurrently","What is concurrently?",[12,32,33],{},"In short, it's a tool that lets you run multiple commands \"in parallel\".",[12,35,36,37,41,42,45],{},"A lot of people try ",[38,39,40],"code",{},"watch-js"," && ",[38,43,44],{},"watch-css",", but that's sequential — it has to wait for the previous command to finish (process exit) before running the next one. Commands like watchers or dev servers never finish, which blocks everything downstream. So you end up opening several terminals to run them.",[12,47,48],{},"To work around this, opening one project meant opening multiple terminals. On a project I inherited, I needed all of these:",[50,51,52,59,65,71,77],"ul",{},[53,54,55,58],"li",{},[38,56,57],{},"npm run dev:backend",": backend API server",[53,60,61,64],{},[38,62,63],{},"npm run dev:ejs",": frontend EJS template server",[53,66,67,70],{},[38,68,69],{},"npm run watch:styles",": watch CSS file changes",[53,72,73,76],{},[38,74,75],{},"npm run watch:scripts",": watch JavaScript file changes",[53,78,79,82],{},[38,80,81],{},"npm run db:server",": database service",[12,84,85],{},"The frontend parts can be unified using Webpack, Vite, or Gulp to watch all file changes. But backend and database can't be folded into that, so you still need multiple terminals.",[12,87,88,89,91,92,91,95,97,98,100],{},"So at minimum you need three terminals (",[38,90,57],{},", ",[38,93,94],{},"npm run dev:frontend",[38,96,81],{},"). That's annoying and wasteful, so this post introduces ",[38,99,17],{},".",[12,102,103,104,106],{},"The whole point of ",[38,105,17],{}," is to let you run multiple commands in one terminal, with auto-managed output so you can easily see what each command is doing.",[20,108,110],{"id":109},"how-to-use-concurrently","How to use concurrently",[12,112,113,114,117,118,121],{},"Usage is dead simple. I strongly recommend installing it into your project so you can use it directly in ",[38,115,116],{},"package.json","'s ",[38,119,120],{},"scripts"," block. The official docs mention global install, but project install keeps versions consistent across projects.",[123,124,129],"pre",{"className":125,"code":126,"language":127,"meta":128,"style":128},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","# npm\nnpm install concurrently --save-dev\n\n# yarn\nyarn add concurrently --dev\n\n# pnpm\npnpm add concurrently --save-dev\n","bash","",[38,130,131,140,158,165,171,185,190,196],{"__ignoreMap":128},[132,133,136],"span",{"class":134,"line":135},"line",1,[132,137,139],{"class":138},"sQrFR","# npm\n",[132,141,143,147,151,154],{"class":134,"line":142},2,[132,144,146],{"class":145},"s_sBn","npm",[132,148,150],{"class":149},"sTRMh"," install",[132,152,153],{"class":149}," concurrently",[132,155,157],{"class":156},"sCcAr"," --save-dev\n",[132,159,161],{"class":134,"line":160},3,[132,162,164],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":163},true,"\n",[132,166,168],{"class":134,"line":167},4,[132,169,170],{"class":138},"# yarn\n",[132,172,174,177,180,182],{"class":134,"line":173},5,[132,175,176],{"class":145},"yarn",[132,178,179],{"class":149}," add",[132,181,153],{"class":149},[132,183,184],{"class":156}," --dev\n",[132,186,188],{"class":134,"line":187},6,[132,189,164],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":163},[132,191,193],{"class":134,"line":192},7,[132,194,195],{"class":138},"# pnpm\n",[132,197,199,202,204,206],{"class":134,"line":198},8,[132,200,201],{"class":145},"pnpm",[132,203,179],{"class":149},[132,205,153],{"class":149},[132,207,157],{"class":156},[12,209,210,211,213,214,216],{},"Open ",[38,212,116],{}," and add a new command to ",[38,215,120],{},":",[123,218,222],{"className":219,"code":220,"language":221,"meta":128,"style":128},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\"scripts\": {\n  \"dev:all\": \"concurrently \\\"npm run dev:frontend\\\" \\\"npm run dev:backend\\\" \\\"npm run db:server\\\"\",\n  \"dev:frontend\": \"webpack serve\",\n  \"dev:backend\": \"node server.js\",\n  \"dev:db\": \"mongod --dbpath .\u002Fdata\u002Fdb\"\n}\n","json",[38,223,224,233,272,284,296,306],{"__ignoreMap":128},[132,225,226,229],{"class":134,"line":135},[132,227,228],{"class":149},"\"scripts\"",[132,230,232],{"class":231},"sMAXC",": {\n",[132,234,235,239,242,245,249,251,253,256,258,260,262,264,266,269],{"class":134,"line":142},[132,236,238],{"class":237},"sKpQp","  \"dev:all\"",[132,240,241],{"class":231},": ",[132,243,244],{"class":149},"\"concurrently ",[132,246,248],{"class":247},"sWyjQ","\\\"",[132,250,94],{"class":149},[132,252,248],{"class":247},[132,254,255],{"class":247}," \\\"",[132,257,57],{"class":149},[132,259,248],{"class":247},[132,261,255],{"class":247},[132,263,81],{"class":149},[132,265,248],{"class":247},[132,267,268],{"class":149},"\"",[132,270,271],{"class":231},",\n",[132,273,274,277,279,282],{"class":134,"line":160},[132,275,276],{"class":237},"  \"dev:frontend\"",[132,278,241],{"class":231},[132,280,281],{"class":149},"\"webpack serve\"",[132,283,271],{"class":231},[132,285,286,289,291,294],{"class":134,"line":167},[132,287,288],{"class":237},"  \"dev:backend\"",[132,290,241],{"class":231},[132,292,293],{"class":149},"\"node server.js\"",[132,295,271],{"class":231},[132,297,298,301,303],{"class":134,"line":173},[132,299,300],{"class":237},"  \"dev:db\"",[132,302,241],{"class":231},[132,304,305],{"class":149},"\"mongod --dbpath .\u002Fdata\u002Fdb\"\n",[132,307,308],{"class":134,"line":187},[132,309,310],{"class":231},"}\n",[12,312,313,314,317],{},"Now ",[38,315,316],{},"npm run dev:all"," runs all three commands at the same time in one terminal.",[20,319,321],{"id":320},"simplifying-with-wildcards","Simplifying with wildcards",[12,323,324],{},"If your scripts have consistent naming, you can simplify further:",[123,326,328],{"className":219,"code":327,"language":221,"meta":128,"style":128},"\"scripts\": {\n  \"dev:all\": \"concurrently \\\"npm run dev:*\\\"\",\n  \"dev:frontend\": \"webpack serve\",\n  \"dev:backend\": \"node server.js\",\n  \"dev:db\": \"mongod --dbpath .\u002Fdata\u002Fdb\" \n}\n",[38,329,330,336,355,365,375,387],{"__ignoreMap":128},[132,331,332,334],{"class":134,"line":135},[132,333,228],{"class":149},[132,335,232],{"class":231},[132,337,338,340,342,344,346,349,351,353],{"class":134,"line":142},[132,339,238],{"class":237},[132,341,241],{"class":231},[132,343,244],{"class":149},[132,345,248],{"class":247},[132,347,348],{"class":149},"npm run dev:*",[132,350,248],{"class":247},[132,352,268],{"class":149},[132,354,271],{"class":231},[132,356,357,359,361,363],{"class":134,"line":160},[132,358,276],{"class":237},[132,360,241],{"class":231},[132,362,281],{"class":149},[132,364,271],{"class":231},[132,366,367,369,371,373],{"class":134,"line":167},[132,368,288],{"class":237},[132,370,241],{"class":231},[132,372,293],{"class":149},[132,374,271],{"class":231},[132,376,377,379,381,384],{"class":134,"line":173},[132,378,300],{"class":237},[132,380,241],{"class":231},[132,382,383],{"class":149},"\"mongod --dbpath .\u002Fdata\u002Fdb\"",[132,385,386],{"class":231}," \n",[132,388,389],{"class":134,"line":187},[132,390,310],{"class":231},[392,393,394],"blockquote",{},[12,395,396,397,400],{},"concurrently auto-detects all commands prefixed with ",[38,398,399],{},"dev:"," and runs them together.",[20,402,404],{"id":403},"auto-kill-other-commands","Auto-kill other commands",[12,406,407,408,411],{},"One more useful one — ",[38,409,410],{},"kill-others",". When one command exits (typically due to an error), it kills all the other commands:",[123,413,414],{"className":219,"code":327,"language":221,"meta":128,"style":128},[38,415,416,422,440,450,460,470],{"__ignoreMap":128},[132,417,418,420],{"class":134,"line":135},[132,419,228],{"class":149},[132,421,232],{"class":231},[132,423,424,426,428,430,432,434,436,438],{"class":134,"line":142},[132,425,238],{"class":237},[132,427,241],{"class":231},[132,429,244],{"class":149},[132,431,248],{"class":247},[132,433,348],{"class":149},[132,435,248],{"class":247},[132,437,268],{"class":149},[132,439,271],{"class":231},[132,441,442,444,446,448],{"class":134,"line":160},[132,443,276],{"class":237},[132,445,241],{"class":231},[132,447,281],{"class":149},[132,449,271],{"class":231},[132,451,452,454,456,458],{"class":134,"line":167},[132,453,288],{"class":237},[132,455,241],{"class":231},[132,457,293],{"class":149},[132,459,271],{"class":231},[132,461,462,464,466,468],{"class":134,"line":173},[132,463,300],{"class":237},[132,465,241],{"class":231},[132,467,383],{"class":149},[132,469,386],{"class":231},[132,471,472],{"class":134,"line":187},[132,473,310],{"class":231},[12,475,476,477,100],{},"You can also heavily customize how output is rendered — I'll skip those details, just check the official docs: ",[478,479,17],"a",{"href":480,"rel":481},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.npmjs.com\u002Fpackage\u002Fconcurrently",[482],"nofollow",[484,485,486],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}",{"title":128,"searchDepth":142,"depth":142,"links":488},[489,490,491,492,493],{"id":22,"depth":142,"text":23},{"id":29,"depth":142,"text":30},{"id":109,"depth":142,"text":110},{"id":320,"depth":142,"text":321},{"id":403,"depth":142,"text":404},"Nodejs","2026-01-13 09:45:28","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Frun-multi